if you want to get a executeable file to run in host
  you can operate as follow:
  make;
  make install;

you can get a file named "server" in local directory that can run in host as a server,
and you also get a server deamon program in local directory named "mydeamon";

if you want to get a executeable file to run in a ARM machine
  you can operate as follow;
  make host=arm-linux-;
  make install_arm host=arm-linux-;

you can get a file named "server_arm" in local directory that can run in host as a server,
and you also get a server deamon program in local directory named "mydeamon_arm";


